        <div class="rivertext">
            <h1>A beautiful place to rest and have fun</h1>
            <p id="pbody">Jarabacoa is often referred to as the "City of Everlasting Spring" due to its mild climate year-round. 
                <br>The town is surrounded by stunning mountains, rivers, and waterfalls, making it a paradise for nature lovers and adventure enthusiasts. 
                <br>From hiking and horseback riding to white-water rafting and exploring coffee plantations, there's something for everyone to enjoy.</p>
            <p>For the adventure seekers, white-water rafting on the Yaque del Norte River is a must-try experience. 
                <br>The river's rapids offer a thrilling ride while you enjoy breathtaking views of the surrounding landscapes.</p>
                <p>You can take leisurely walks through the town's charming streets, visit local markets to experience the vibrant culture, 
                    <br>or embark on a peaceful horseback ride through the scenic countryside.</p>
            <p>One of the highlights is Salto de Jimenoa, a stunning waterfall that you can reach after a short hike. 
                <br>The cool, misty atmosphere around the falls is truly refreshing. Additionally, don't miss the opportunity to explore the Jarabacoa Botanical Garden, 
                <br>which features a diverse collection of native plants and flowers.</p> 
        </div>
